      "Use ": "使用",
      "Use accusative when there is movement to a new location, dative when staying in place.": "当移动到新位置时使用宾格，当保持原地时使用与格。",
      "Use lan directly before the present tense verb to negate future actions.": "在现在时动词前直接使用lan来否定未来行为。",
      "Use present continuous for actions happening right now.": "使用现在进行时来描述正在发生的行为。",
      "Use who for people, which for things. That is used only in defining relative clauses.": "用who指人，用which指事物。that仅用于定语从句中。",
      "Used after certain verbs, adjectives, and nouns.": "在某些动词、形容词和名词之后使用。",
      "Used after prepositions (e.g. con cui = with which, di cui = of which).": "在介词之后使用（例如con cui = with which，di cui = of which）。",
      "Used for actions in progress being acted upon a subject.": "用于描述正在进行的行为对某一主体的影响。",
      "Used for completed actions in the past.": "用于描述过去已经完成的行为。",
      "Used for habits, descriptions, and ongoing states in the past.": "用于描述过去的习惯、描述和正在进行的状态。",
      "Used for hypothetical situations in the present (e.g. If I won... I would...).": "用于描述现在的假设情况（例如如果我赢了... 我会...）。",
      "Used for imaginary or highly unlikely present/future situations.": "用于描述现在或未来的想象或极不可能的情况。",
      "Used for the recipient of an action, or after specific dative prepositions.": "用于描述行为的接受者，或在特定的与格介词之后。",
      "Used for wishes, polite requests, and hypothetical conditions.": "用于描述愿望、礼貌请求和假设条件。",
      "Used in hypothetical conditions (with ": "在假设条件中使用（与...",
      "Used to compare two things where A is more adjective than B.": "用于比较两件事物，其中A比B更具有某一特性。",
      "Used to connect clauses and avoid repetition of nouns.": "用于连接从句并避免名词的重复。",
      "Used to describe actions that will be in progress at a specific time in the future.": "用于描述将在未来某一特定时间正在进行的行为。",
      "Used to describe an action completed before another past action.": "用于描述在另一个过去行为之前已经完成的行为。",
      "Used to describe an action that happened before another action in the past.": "用于描述在过去发生在另一个行为之前的行为。",
      "Used to express a concession or contrast between two clauses.": "用于表达两个从句之间的让步或对比。",
      "Used to express a past situation that is discontinued or completed far in the past.": "用于表达过去已经停止或在很久以前完成的情况。",
      "Used to express desires, doubts, emotions, or recommendations.": "用于表达愿望、怀疑、情感或建议。",
      "Used to express doubt, hope, emotion, opinion, or desire in subordinate clauses.": "用于在从句中表达怀疑、希望、情感、意见或愿望。",
      "Used to express future actions, plans, or predictions.": "用于表达未来行为、计划或预测。",
      "Used to express making or letting someone do an action.": "用于表达使某人做某事或允许某人做某事。",
      "Used to express passive action, often with a nuance of annoyance.": "用于表达被动行为，常带有一丝恼怒的意味。",
      "Used to express polite requests, wishes, hypothetical situations, or advice.": "用于表达礼貌请求、愿望、假设情况或建议。",
      "Used to express possession or association (e.g. the book of the teacher). Noun 1 never takes al- or tanween.": "用于表达所有权或关联（例如老师的书）。名词1永远不带al-或tanween。",
      "Used to express probability, conjecture, or polite suggestion.": "用于表达可能性、推测或礼貌建议。",
      "Used to express surprise, rhetoric, or reminder (meaning ": "用于表达惊讶、修辞或提醒（含义...",
      "Used to politely ask someone to do something.": "用于礼貌地请求某人做某事。",
      "Used to show an action occurred before another past event.": "用于表明一个行为发生在另一个过去事件之前。",
      "Used when recalling or reporting a past experience directly observed.": "用于回忆或报告直接观察到的过去经历。",
      "Used when the agent performing the action is not specified.": "当执行行为的主体未指定时使用。",
      "Used when the focus is on the action or the receiver, not who does it.": "当焦点在行为或接受者上，而不是谁执行时使用。",
      "Used when the subject has something done by someone else (e.g. to have/get something done).": "当主体由别人做某事时使用（例如让某人做某事）。",
